    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="437"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-13T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 13, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Your 64, March 10, 9 a.m. For McBride. In order to insure that the fullest
                    protection against disease will be accorded to the United States armed forces
                    and with the view to improving the health of the native population, the War
                    Department explains that there should be a degree of cooperation between
                    Liberian health officials and the United States forces similar to that now
                    existing in the United States betweeen local, state and federal health agencies
                    and army authorities. It is felt by the War Department that the United States
                    forces should have under their control all strictly military areas, as well as
                    any contiguous areas which would present a health hazard to American troops by
                    reason of existing conditions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
